President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Alan B. Krueger as a member of the Council of Economic Advisers (CEA). Once confirmed, Krueger will be designated as the Chairman of CEA. Krueger, a leading economist, will bring his extensive knowledge and experience to the President's economic team to address the challenges of job creation and economic growth. The CEA provides economic advice to the President on both domestic and international economic policy, using research and empirical evidence. Krueger is currently a professor at Princeton University and has previously served in various positions, including Assistant Secretary for Economic Policy and Chief Economist at the U.S. Department of the Treasury.